@@$TJvScrollingLabel
<TITLE TJvScrollingLabel overview>
<GROUP JVCL.Labels>
  TJvScrollingLabel is a label that can scroll it's text.
  
  * Specify the scroll text by setting the property Text.
  * Use ScrollInterval to specify the amount of time in milliseconds between scroll events.
  * Set Scrolling to True at design-time, or set this property at run-time to start the scrolling.
  * Use ScrollDirection to change the default scroll direction.
  * Use OnMouseEnter and OnMouseLeave to alter the controls look or behavoir, when the user moves the
    mouse pointer over the control.
