@@TJvScrollingLabel
<GROUP TJvScrollingLabel>
Summary
  Label that can scroll it's text.
Description
  The TJvScrollingLabel component functions like TLabel, except that it can scroll it's text.
  
  Specify the label scroll text by property Text. Use ScrollInterval to specify the amount of time in
  milliseconds between scroll events. Use Scrolling to enable or disable scrolling. Set ScrollDirection
  to specify the scroll direction.
----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
@@TJvScrollingLabel.Create
Summary
  Creates and initializes an instance of TJvScrollingLabel.
Description
  Call Create to create an instance of TJvScrollingLabel at runtime. A TJvScrollingLabel placed on a 
  form at design time is created automatically.

  Pass a single Component as a parameter to provide the scrolling label with an Owner that is responsible
  for freeing it.

  Create calls the inherited Create method, creates a timer, and then sets the initial values for the 
  scrolling label as follows: 
  
  * ScrollInterval is set to 50.
  * Scrolling is set to True.
  * NoGrap is set to False.
  * Text is set to the jedi home page.
  * ScrollDirection is set to sdLeftToRight;
  * AutoSize is set to False
Parameters
  AOwner - The owner for the instance of TJvScrollingLabel.
See Also
  Destroy, NoGrap, ScrollDirection, Scrolling, ScrollInterval, Text
----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
@@TJvScrollingLabel.Destroy
Summary
  Destroys an instance of TJvScrollingLabel.
Description
  Do not call Destroy directly in an application. Instead, call Free. Free verifies that the 
  TJvScrollingLabel object is not nil and only then calls Destroy.
  
  Destroy frees the timer.
Parameters
  None.
See Also
  Create
