@@TJvScrollingLabel.OnMouseEnter
Summary
  Occurs when the mouse pointer moves over the label.
Description
  Write an OnMouseEnter event handler to take specific action when the user moves the mouse over the
  label. For example, you can use this event to change the font color when the mouse is over the
  label, and then use the OnMouseLeave event to change it back when the mouse moves off the label.
See Also
  OnMouseLeave 
----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
@@TJvScrollingLabel.OnMouseLeave
Summary
  Occurs when the mouse pointer moves off the label.
Description
  Write an OnMouseLeave event handler to take specific action when the user moves the mouse off the
  label. For example, you can use this event to undo changes that were made in an OnMouseEnter
  event handler.
See Also
  OnMouseEnter
----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
@@TJvScrollingLabel.OnParentColorChange
Summary
  Occurs when the color property for the parent of the label changes.
Description
  Write an OnParentColorChange event to take specific action when the ParentColor property changes.
See Also 
  OnCtl3DChanged
----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
@@TJvScrollingLabel.ScrollDirection
Summary
  Indicates the scroll direction for the text.
Description
  Set ScrollDirection to indicate the scroll direction for the text. The direction can be: left to right
  or right to left.
  
  The default value of ScrollDirection is sdLeftToRight.
See Also
  NoGrap, Scrolling, ScrollInterval, Text
----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
@@TJvScrollingLabel.Scrolling
Summary
  Indicates whether the label is scrolling the text.
Description
  Set Scrolling to True to scroll the text of the control. Set Scrolling to False to interrupt 
  the control when it is scrolling it's text.

  The text of the control will only scroll runtime.
See Also
  NoGrap, ScrollDirection, ScrollInterval, Text
----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
@@TJvScrollingLabel.ScrollInterval
Summary
  Determines the amount of time, in milliseconds, that passes before the label text is scrolled.
Description
  Interval determines how frequently the scroll event occurs. Each time the specified interval passes,
  the label text scrolls.

  Use Interval to specify any cardinal value as the interval between scroll events. The default value 
  is 50 (1/20 second).

  A 0 value is valid, however the label text will not scroll for a value of 0.
See Also
  NoGrap, ScrollDirection, Scrolling, ScrollInterval, Text
----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
@@TJvScrollingLabel.Text
Summary
  Contains the scroll text string.
Description
  Use the Text property to read the scroll text of the control or specify a new string for the Text value. 
  By default, Text is the url to the jedi home page.
See Also
  NoGrap, ScrollDirection, Scrolling, ScrollInterval